An Act to modernize cannabis retail operations.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 4 of chapter 94G subsection (a1/2)(xxix), as so appearing, is
2 hereby amended by inserting in subsection (a1/2)(xxix)(6) after the word “marijuana” the
3 following words:-
4 provided that the commission shall not prohibit advertising, marketing and branding of
5 sales, discounts, and customer loyalty programs within a Marijuana Establishment, through a
6 delivery service, on an internet website maintained by a Marijuana Establishment, or through an
7 opt-in email marketing campaign;
8 SECTION 2. The commission shall promulgate or amend regulations as necessary to be
9 consistent with Section 1 not later than 365 days from the effective date of this act.
